---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="For Resort Hotels — Half-Board at Your Standard"
  description="Avorix for resort hotels with half-board: secure your menus, train your team, bridge staff gaps. Cook app, training, and staff from one source."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-28 pb-16 px-6 bg-gradient-to-b from-brand-50/50 to-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-sm font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-brand-500 mb-4">For Resort Hotels with Half-Board</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-neutral-900 leading-tight mb-6">
        Half-Board at Your Standard.<br />Every Evening. No Matter Who's in the Kitchen.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Avorix secures your house menus as a step-by-step system, trains your team, and bridges staff gaps with real chefs. So every guest gets the dinner they booked for. <strong class="text-neutral-900">Even without trained chefs.</strong>
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mb-6">
        <a href="/en/contact" data-cta-location="hotels-hero" class="bg-brand-500 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-bold hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors inline-block">Book a Demo</a>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 text-sm">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-neutral-50 border border-brand-200 text-neutral-800 rounded-full px-4 py-2 font-semibold">&#10003; Official Staff Leasing Permit</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Half-Board Is a Promise -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">Half-Board Is a Promise.</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">A full menu for the entire house every evening.</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Your guests booked half-board. They expect a complete menu every evening that matches the house. Not just anything — your standard.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">The review decides the next booking.</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Guests rate the food. One weak evening is enough for a bad review. And bad reviews cost bookings.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Key staff leave, seasonal staff arrive.</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">New faces in the kitchen every season. The knowledge leaves with the chef; the new one starts from zero.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mt-6">When the kitchen wobbles, the reviews wobble. When the reviews wobble, the bookings wobble. The kitchen isn't a sideshow — it's the foundation of your occupancy.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our System -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Our System: Secure Menus, Train Teams, Bridge Gaps.</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 max-w-3xl mb-8">Think of a sat-nav. A sat-nav gets any driver to the destination, even if they don't know the route. Avorix does the same in your kitchen: it guides any kitchen worker to the finished menu, even if they've never cooked it before.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">1 &middot; System</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">An experienced Avorix chef comes to your house and documents your menus. Every dish is broken down into simple steps, with photos, precise quantities, and timing. Everything goes into the Cook App.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">2 &middot; Training</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Your team learns to work with the system. Right at the stove, during operations. The Avorix chef trains them until your team runs the menus independently.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">3 &middot; Reinforcement</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">When staff calls in sick or the season begins: Avorix employs permanent chefs that we lease to you legally. They know the system and are productive from day one.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 space-y-3 text-neutral-600">
        <p><strong class="text-neutral-900">And your costs?</strong> Trained chefs are expensive — if you can find them at all. With Avorix, trained-up staff cook your menus at your standard.</p>
        <p><strong class="text-neutral-900">And your guests?</strong> They notice nothing. Your guests experience your kitchen and your recipes. On request, we contractually guarantee that we won't mention your property as a reference anywhere.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-6">
        <a href="/en/contact" data-cta-location="hotels-system" class="border-2 border-brand-500 text-brand-500 px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-bold hover:bg-brand-50 transition-colors inline-block">How the Avorix System Works</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Menu Cycles -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Half-Board Cycles: Made for This System.</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Half-board in most houses means a menu cycle that repeats every few weeks. Monday soup and roast, Tuesday fish, Wednesday pasta. This is ideal for our system, because recurring menus can be documented and trained especially cleanly.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">With the <strong class="text-neutral-900">Menu Planner</strong> in the Cook App, you plan each calendar week: which dishes, how many portions, which specials. Proven weeks can simply be copied into the next.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">The <strong class="text-neutral-900">Portion Calculator</strong> scales automatically: 80 guests instead of 60? All quantities adjust.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">From the finished menu plan, the app generates the <strong class="text-neutral-900">shopping list</strong> at the push of a button: items, quantities, units, estimated prices. No scraps of paper, nothing forgotten.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Four Steps -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">How Avorix Comes to Your Hotel. In Four Steps.</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-brand-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold shrink-0">1</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900">Conversation</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-1">30 minutes, via video or on-site. You explain how your half-board is structured, how large the team is, where it gets stuck. We honestly say whether Avorix fits your house.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-brand-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold shrink-0">2</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900">Documentation</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-1">An Avorix chef comes to your house, cooks with your team, and documents your menus. Every dish goes into the app: steps, photos, quantities, timing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-brand-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold shrink-0">3</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900">Training</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-1">Your team learns to work with the system. Right at the stove, during operations. The Avorix chef stays until your crew runs the menus independently.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-brand-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold shrink-0">4</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900">Independent</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-1">The app guides your team through every evening. New menus are added by you or by us. And when staff is short: one call is enough.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-8">The quiet weeks between seasons are ideal for documentation and training. Start the next season prepared.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pilot -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">As a Pilot Operation at Half the Price.</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">In 2026, we're looking for a handful of resort hotels to be the first to use Avorix. Pilot operations receive the full system at significantly reduced rates. In return, we learn from your operation and continue to improve our system.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">You take no risk: in the first conversation, we transparently calculate the cost. No fine print.</p>
      <a href="/en/pilot-program" data-cta-location="hotels-pilot" class="bg-brand-500 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-bold hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors inline-block">To the Pilot Program</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <details open class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4">
          <summary class="font-bold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">We have a mix of half-board and a la carte. Does that work?</summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-3">Yes. The app handles both. Your half-board menus are planned in the Menu Planner; your a la carte dishes sit in the Recipe Library. Both run in parallel.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4">
          <summary class="font-bold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">How often do the menus change?</summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-3">As often as you like. Many houses work with weekly cycles that repeat every two to four weeks. In the Menu Planner, you copy proven weeks and adjust individual dishes.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4">
          <summary class="font-bold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">What does our head chef think of this?</summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-3">In our experience, the head chef is the first to see the benefit. Their knowledge is finally captured, their team works more independently, and when someone calls in sick, they're not left alone.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4">
          <summary class="font-bold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">Does this work for breakfast too?</summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-3">Yes. Breakfast buffet, mise en place, replenishment — everything can be documented and trained just like the evening menu.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4">
          <summary class="font-bold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">How quickly can we start before the season?</summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-3">Ideally a few weeks before season start. That leaves time for documentation and training at a calm pace. In urgent cases, we can move faster.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Your Guests Booked Half-Board. Give Them a Reason to Come Back Every Evening.</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">30 minutes, free, no obligation. We'll look at your half-board and honestly tell you whether Avorix fits your house.</p>
      <a href="/en/contact" data-cta-location="hotels-final" class="bg-brand-500 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-xl font-bold text-lg hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors inline-block">Book a Demo</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
